<!-- doc/src/sgml/wal-for-extensions.sgml -->

<chapter id="wal-for-extensions">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ee0af51d0030e9bd4a44b2cdae89e3a9 sig_cn_org=769c06cc6869b09b9c75abbbec41b98a source=17.5 
 <title>Write Ahead Logging for Extensions</title>
________________________________________________________-->
 <title>扩展的预写日志</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ee0af51d0030e9bd4a44b2cdae89e3a9 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3d6a71d93d358f7d4c4568d6bbbf89eb sig_cn_org=5ed77f25f528f9ceee2e081479c4951e source=17.5 
  <para>
   Certain extensions, principally extensions that implement custom access
   methods, may need to perform write-ahead logging in order to ensure
   crash-safety. <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> provides two ways
   for extensions to achieve this goal.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   某些扩展，主要是实现自定义访问方法的扩展，可能需要执行预写日志以确保
   崩溃安全。<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>提供了两种方式让扩展实现
   这一目标。
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3d6a71d93d358f7d4c4568d6bbbf89eb -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=aab5cc2a9ace4bf0254e9ce32f0a6174 sig_cn_org=d68efecbba4174fbd4153ea3c0c46973 source=17.5 
  <para>
   First, extensions can choose to use <link linkend="generic-wal">generic
   WAL</link>, a special type of WAL record which describes changes to pages
   in a generic way. This method is simple to implement and does not require
   that an extension library be loaded in order to apply the records. However,
   generic WAL records will be ignored when performing logical decoding.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   首先，扩展可以选择使用<link linkend="generic-wal">通用 WAL</link>，这是一种特殊类型的 WAL
   记录，用于以通用方式描述页面的更改。此方法实现简单，且在应用记录时不需要加载扩展库。
   但是，执行逻辑解码时会忽略通用 WAL 记录。
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=aab5cc2a9ace4bf0254e9ce32f0a6174 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=4343138dbc4c783160a227fd29a240f6 sig_cn_org=5f1336f5adcfa31ea39194e1fe4e044f source=17.5 
  <para>
   Second, extensions can choose to use a <link linkend="custom-rmgr">custom
   resource manager</link>. This method is more flexible, supports logical
   decoding, and can sometimes generate much smaller write-ahead log records
   than would be possible with generic WAL. However, it is more complex for an
   extension to implement.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   其次，扩展可以选择使用<link linkend="custom-rmgr">自定义资源管理器</link>。
   这种方法更灵活，支持逻辑解码，有时能生成比通用WAL更小得多的预写日志记录。
   但是，对于扩展来说，实现起来更复杂。
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=4343138dbc4c783160a227fd29a240f6 -->

&generic-wal;
&custom-rmgr;

</chapter>
